		<h1>Sleep Stats</h1>
		<p>
			<li>Ages 13-18 need 9.25 hours a night</li>
			<li>Try to maintain a regular sleep schedule</li>
			<li>Avoid oversleeping on weekends</li>
			<li>Take early afternoon naps of 15-20 mins</li>
			<li>Turn off screens</li>
			<li>Keep your room cool, quiet, and dark at night</li>
			<li>Let light come in the morning to signal your body to wake up</li>
			<li>Avoid looking at screens before you try to fall asleep</li>
			
			<br><br>
			<p>Click </p><a href="http://www.nationwidechildrens.org/sleep-in-adolescents">here</a><p> or </p><a href="https://sleepfoundation.org/sleep-topics/teens-and-sleep/page/0/1">here</a><p> for more information on sleep.</p>
		</p>
